        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 5 at 6:53PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 653 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Adams Run, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Summerville, Edisto Beach, Johns Island, West Ashley, Hollywood,
Folly Beach, Ravenel, Seabrook Island, Kiawah Island and Meggett.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay tuned to NOAA Weather Radio All Hazards, TV or your local news
source for the latest information from the National Weather Service.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
